==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pedionomus
<hw>Pedionomus</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A genus of birds including
the <stype>plains wanderer</stype> (<spn>Pedionomus torquatus</spn>) of
New South Wales as its only species. It is the only genus of the family
<fam>Pedionomidae</fam> of the order <ord>Passeriformes</ord> and the
plains wanderer is the only species in the family. The total world
population (as of ca. 2000) is estimated to be 5 to 10 thousand.</def>
<note>See also http://www.philipmaher.com/plains.htm.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus Pedionomus.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pedipalp</ent>⟦br⟧
